Notes/Domino is working as designed. It can be critical that the domain information be appended, as without it, mail may not route as expected in some scenarios.

Enhancement requests to improve the logic in this area have been made to Quality Engineering as SPR# NGRT4M7H67 and SPR# MCHT4LYK85.

If you want multiple domain information to remain in e-mail, you can add the variable "NoOptimizeLocalRouting=1" to the notes.ini file in the Notes client and restart Notes.

There is also an unsupported workaround that will prevent the Notes Internet domain from being added to Internet addresses, but it may result in delivery failures under some scenarios. This involves modifying the formulas in the InheritedFrom and InheritedAltFrom fields in the Reply and Reply With History forms as follows:
```
Who := @If
(@IsAvailable(Principal) & Principal != "";
@IsAvailable(From);
@Author

@If (@IsAvailable(FromDomain) & (@Middle(who; "@";".")="");
Who
```

